OL,3,CParts of WW2 bomb found in Ards on
OL,4,Cdisplay in museum
OL,6,FFragments of a World War Two bomb that
OL,7,Fwas discovered in a housing
OL,8,Fdevelopment in Newtownards in August
OL,9,F2024 are now on display at a museum in
OL,10,FBelfast.
OL,12,FHundreds of families had to leave
OL,13,Ftheir homes in Rivenwood for five days
OL,14,Fwhile the historic device was made
OL,15,Fsafe by bomb experts who carried out a
OL,16,Fcontrolled explosion.
OL,18,FA vast crater was left following the
OL,19,Fexplosion, as well as some small
OL,20,Fpieces of the bomb itself.
