OL,6,FThey are now being showcased at the NI
OL,7,FWar Memorial Museum, given people the
OL,8,Fopportunity to "almost reach into the
OL,9,Fpast".
OL,11,FDr James O'Neill, the museum's
OL,12,Fcollections officer, told UTV: "At the
OL,13,Ftime we contacted the military and
OL,14,Fasked, quite cheekily actually; 'After
OL,15,Fyou blow the device, could we have
OL,16,Fsome remains of the bomb?', and that's
OL,17,Fexactly what they did.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/4
