OL,6,F"In the case of the Rivenwood bomb, it
OL,7,Fstruck the bedrock and in all
OL,8,Fpossibility the shock of that damaged
OL,9,Fthe two fuses that were set to make
OL,10,Fthe bomb detonate," said Dr O'Neill.
OL,12,F"There were almost 300kg of explosives
OL,13,Finside the bomb, so that maybe shows
OL,14,Fpeople that it wasn't a small bomb."
OL,16,FAs for the origins of the bomb, Dr
OL,17,FO'Neill said: "We are 100% sure it
OL,18,Fcame on the 1941 Easter Tuesday raid,
OL,19,Fbut which bomber dropped it or which
OL,20,Funit dropped it, we don't know."
